ture trium liberorum By the Lex Iulia et Papia Poppaea, as the revised law passed 9 ab. was called (Tac. Ann. iii 25, Suet. Aug. 34), certain disquali· fications were imposed on caelibes be- tween the ages of twenty and sixty, and

on orbi (rie. men married but childless); Gaius, ii 111 and 286. Thus caelibes could not talre inheritances or legacies except from the nearest relatives; orbi could only talre half the amount. Privi- leges, on the other hand, were given to those who were married (mariti), and es· pecially to those who had three children m Rome, or four in Italy, or five in the provinces; Just. Inst. Tit. 253 Orell. 3750.
